    <td>
<b>
	<h1>Ingredients</h1>
<input type=checkbox name="test" value=2 > 
Teaspoon oil<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=2 > Clove garlic (finely chopped)<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=½ > Onion (finely chopped)<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=½ > Carrot (finely chopped)<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=2 > 
Tablespoon capsicum (chopped)<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=½ > Tomato (chopped)<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=2 > 
Tablespoon sweet corn<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=¼ > 
Teaspoon turmeric<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=½ > 
Teaspoon chilli powder<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=¼ > 
Teaspoon salt<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=1 > Cup water<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=1 > Pack maggi noodles<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=1 > Pack tastemaker<br>
 <input type=checkbox name="test" value=2 > 
Tablespoon coriander (finely chopped)<br> </b></td>

<td> <h1>Cooking Process</h1> <h4>1 firstly, in pan heat 2 tsp oil and saute 2 clove garlic and ½ onion.
2 add ½ carrot, 2 tbsp capsicum, ½ tomato and 2 tbsp sweet corn.
<br><br>3 saute until the vegetables turn crunchy.
<br><br>4 further add ¼ tsp turmeric, ½ tsp chilli powder, ¼ tsp salt and saute until the spices turn aromatic.
<br><br>5 add 1 cup water and get to a boil.
<br><br>6 now bread 1 pack maggi noodles roughly and add 1 pack tastemaker.
<br><br>7 mix well and boil for 2 minutes or until the noodles are cooked well.
<br><br>8 finally, add 2 tbsp coriander and enjoy masaledar maggi. </h4></td>
